How do i convert this to integer
To convert `createPixDto.duration` to an integer in TypeScript, you can use the built-in `parseInt()` function. Here's how you can modify your code:

```typescript
class PixMapper {
    static toBancoDoBrasil(createPixDto: CreatePixDto): BancoDoBrasilRequestDTO {
        return {
            // Other properties mapped here...
            duration: parseInt(createPixDto.duration, 10),
            // Ensure the radix is set to 10 for decimal conversion
        };
    }
}
```

This will convert `createPixDto.duration` from a string to an integer using base 10.
